beanReadBeforeInit

protected boolean beanReadBeforeInit
Holds information whether readFromBean(*) has been called before this widget is initialized. When this variable is still false by the time init() occurs, the readFromBean() method will be called automatically. This makes using BeanFormWidget more convenient when the bean object is provided to the constructor (by not having to call the read method manually). However, it also prevents writing over form data when a programmer has already called readFromBean(Object).

Since:
2.0

addBeanSubForm

public BeanFormWidget<?> addBeanSubForm(String path)
Adds a bean-sub-form with given path. Since this class is BeanFormWidget, the path must map to bean properties and property type is evaluated and used as the type of the bean-sub-form.

Since Aranea 2.0, the given path may be nested where path elements (separated by dots) are used for bean-sub-form creation or for adding new sub-forms with the path element as the sub-form ID.

Parameters:
path - The (simple or nested) path of bean-sub-form to add where path must also correspond to bean properties. Nested path has dots separating sub-form IDs in the order they will be created (the second sub-form will be the sub-form of the first sub-form, etc).
Returns:
The last created sub-form, or the current bean (when the path is empty).
See Also:
FormWidget.addSubForm(String), addSimpleBeanSubForm(String)

addBeanSubForm

@Deprecated

                                                       Class<E> dataType)
Deprecated. Use addSimpleBeanSubForm(String, Class) instead.

Adds a bean sub form with the given id and with given dataType. Does not support nested fields! Also, the id must match a property of the bean this bean-form-widget represents.

Parameters:
id - The ID the sub-form will have.
dataType - The type the sub-form represents when converted to the target bean.
Returns:
The created sub-form.

addSimpleBeanSubForm

public BeanFormWidget<?> addSimpleBeanSubForm(String id)
Adds a bean sub form with the given id. Does not support nested fields! Also, the id must match a property of the bean this bean-form-widget represents. The property type for sub-form will be automatically resolved using the target bean.

Parameters:
id - The ID the sub-form will have.
Returns:
The created sub-form.
Since:

addSimpleBeanSubForm

public <E> BeanFormWidget<E> addSimpleBeanSubForm(String id,
                                                  Class<E> dataType)
Adds a bean-sub-form with the given id and with given dataType. Does not support nested fields! Also, the id must match a property of the bean this bean-form-widget represents. The dataType must be compatible with the property type.

Type Parameters:
E - The type of the class that will be also the type of the BeanFormWidget.
Parameters:
id - The ID the sub-form will have.
dataType - The type the sub-form represents when converted to the target bean.
Returns:
The created sub-form.
Since:
2.0

writeToBean

public T writeToBean(T bean)
Writes form data to given bean. Prefer using writeToBean() instead, when possible, because it makes use of the existing bean object that was provided to this form widget.

Parameters:
bean - An instance of bean where form values will be written.
Returns:
The same bean as provided for input.

getBean

public T getBean()
Provides the bean that was provided for input. Note that the bean may have different property values compared to the state when the form was initialized, because when writeToBean() is used, it updates the bean properties with values from the form.

Returns:
The bean object that was used to initialize this form widget.
